<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/708146-i-have-seen-the-movie-a-while-ago-and-it">I have seen the movie a while ago and it is vague to me. I was curious if this book would be appropriate for my 10 year old son? Thanks!</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_708146'><a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F108229.The_Perfect_Storm">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/708146-i-have-seen-the-movie-a-while-ago-and-it">5 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/708146-i-have-seen-the-movie-a-while-ago-and-it">See all 3 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/26587306-al"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1515463693i/26587306._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/26587306-al">Al</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Reading the book is like watching the extra features on the DVD. The author discusses his research on weather, the sword fishing industry, etc. He int<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Reading the book is like watching the extra features on the DVD. The author discusses his research on weather, the sword fishing industry, etc. He interviewed the Andrea Gail crew's friends, families and neighbors to get an idea for what may have happened and how they would have responded. Wherever possible uses interviews with people who were on scene (the rescue crews, for example) He also discusses some of the history about the boat, and post storm legal actions. More journalistic and less dramatic than the film. If he likes the History or Discovery Channel shows, he'll probably like it. <br /><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

