    <a title="Jennifer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/123884-jennifer"><img alt="Jennifer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1202092052p2/123884.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2846726?book_show_action=true">Jul 08, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jennifer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jennifer" href="/user/show/123884-jennifer">Jennifer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Paperback 9780061013515" href="/book/show/586434.The_Perfect_Storm">review of another edition</a>

          <div><span class="uitext greyText">Recommends it for: </span>
           <span class="uitext reviewText">people who don't mind being depressed and are interested in MA and maritime history</span></div>

        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2846726" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11038067703321003696">This was pretty good and read really quickly, especially toward the end. The quite drawn-out description of what it&apos;s like to drown was terrifying, as well as the description of what the ocean is like in a storm like that. I&apos;m scared of the ocean so I found it oddly fascinating in a horrific way. I also thought that the very real importance of dreams and premonitions was described in the book--crewmen would get a &quot;bad feeling&quot; about going out with a boat and family members would dream about love</span>
  <span id="freeText11038067703321003696" style="display:none">This was pretty good and read really quickly, especially toward the end. The quite drawn-out description of what it's like to drown was terrifying, as well as the description of what the ocean is like in a storm like that. I'm scared of the ocean so I found it oddly fascinating in a horrific way. I also thought that the very real importance of dreams and premonitions was described in the book--crewmen would get a "bad feeling" about going out with a boat and family members would dream about loved ones who were in peril or lost. Overall, there's something weird about reading something so gripping about something so tragic that's a real story--it feels exploitative to be that interested in how it all happened. But the author does a nice job of respecting the family members and the memory of the people who died.<br /><br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="11038067703321003696" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


